            img.img-fluid(src='/public/images/designTwin.png')
          .col-xl-6.col-lg-6
            h5 Integration
            img.img-fluid(src='/public/images/integration.png')
    #accordion
      .card
        #networkinghead.card-header(role='tab', style='background-color: #cd5c5c; color:#f7f7f7;')
          h5.mb-0
            a(data-toggle='collapse' data-target='#network')
              | Networking
        #network.collapse.show(data-parent='#accordion')
          .card-body
            p.d-none.d-sm-block
              ul
                li All the shops are properly networked using gigabit interfaces.
                li Wireless networking will also be supported
                li Required Central computer system will be placed in existing data center
                li A set of various servers will act as data concentrator backbone
                li Push-Pull data logging system will be supported
      .card
        #dataloghead.card-header(role='tab', style='background-color: #cd5c5c; color:#f7f7f7;')
          h5.mb-0
            a.collapsed(data-toggle='collapse' data-target='#datalog')
              | Data Logging
        #datalog.collapse(data-parent='#accordion')
          .card-body
            p.d-none.d-sm-block
              ul
                li All the network ready machines will send data to data concentrator
                li All machines will send health related data also.
                li
                  | A Network Interface Unit(NIU) (one for each Raw machine) will be designed which will push data into data concentrator. This NIU will be wireless ready
                li Data format for standard data will be standardized 
                li Data format for Health data will be standardized 
                li Data frequency will also be standardized (Per machine)
                li
                  | Some data logger units will be placed across the various shop at various strategic point to know the resource health and environment inside a shop.
      .card
        #sohead.card-header(role='tab', style='background-color: #cd5c5c; color:#f7f7f7;')
          h5.mb-0
            a.collapsed(data-toggle='collapse' data-target='#sopti')
              | Schedule Optimization
        #sopti.collapse(data-parent='#accordion')
          .card-body
            p.d-none.d-sm-block
              ul
                li Analysis outcome will provide the optimized usage of every machine.
                li Shop expansion plan will be generated using analysis outcome
      .card
        #utiinhead.card-header(role='tab', style='background-color: #cd5c5c; color:#f7f7f7;')
          h5.mb-0
            a.collapsed(data-toggle='collapse' data-target='#utiin')
              | Inefficiency cum under utilization Indicator
        #utiin.collapse(data-parent='#accordion')
          .card-body
            p.d-none.d-sm-block
              ul
                li Dynamic analysis outcome will predict the Inefficiency pointer
                li It will also indicate under utilization related issues.
      .card
        #pihead.card-header(role='tab', style='background-color: #cd5c5c; color:#f7f7f7;')
          h5.mb-0
            a.collapsed(data-toggle='collapse' data-target='#pindi')
              | Productivity Indicators
        #pindi.collapse(data-parent='#accordion')
          .card-body
            p.d-none.d-sm-block
              ul
                li
                  | Provide the following productivity indicators
                  ul
                    li for machine, shop, plant
                li Current Order Status
                li Capacity to cater future orders
                li Expansion requirement to cater future orders
                li Schedule for expansion in phased manner
      .card
        #healthmohead.card-header(role='tab', style='background-color: #cd5c5c; color:#f7f7f7;')
          h5.mb-0
            a.collapsed(data-toggle='collapse' data-target='#health')
              | Health Monitoring
        #health.collapse(data-parent='#accordion')
          .card-body
            p.d-none.d-sm-block
              ul
                li Monitoring of Machines
                li Monitoring of Process
                li Monitoring of Products
                li
                  | Failures and Down time
                  ul
                    li Machine uptime
                    li Cascaded effect on product line for a given failure
                    li How to achieve failure independence
